---
import { HeroActions } from '../components/marketing/HeroActions'
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="VTO for Shopify | Convert More, Return Less"
  description="AI virtual try-on for Shopify. Let shoppers preview products on themselves and reduce return rates with an async, high-quality try-on flow."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 pt-8 pb-24 sm:px-8 lg:px-10">
    <section class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1.25fr_1fr] lg:items-center">
      <div>
        <p
          class="bg-secondary/80 text-secondary-foreground mb-4 inline-flex rounded-full border px-4 py-1 text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase"
        >
          Shopify App + Modular AI API
        </p>
        <h1
          class="font-display text-4xl leading-tight font-extrabold text-balance sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
        >
          Cut return risk before checkout with <span class="text-primary"
            >real shopper try-ons</span
          >.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-5 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed">
          VTO lets your shoppers upload a photo, try products on in seconds, and
          keep browsing while generation runs in the background. You get higher
          purchase confidence with less cart friction.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8">
          <HeroActions />
        </div>
        <dl class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl border p-4">
            <dt class="text-muted-foreground text-xs tracking-wider uppercase">
              Async first
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-xl font-bold">40s+ safe flow</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl border p-4">
            <dt class="text-muted-foreground text-xs tracking-wider uppercase">
              Model abstraction
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-xl font-bold">normal / advanced</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl border p-4">
            <dt class="text-muted-foreground text-xs tracking-wider uppercase">
              Cost control
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-xl font-bold">Credit-based usage</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-halo bg-card orb-shadow rounded-3xl border p-6">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold">What your shopper sees</h2>
        <ol
          class="text-muted-foreground mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed"
        >
          <li>
            <strong class="text-foreground">1.</strong> Upload one personal image.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-foreground">2.</strong> Tap try-on on a product page.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-foreground">3.</strong> Keep browsing while generation
            runs.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-foreground">4.</strong> Open result and continue to
            checkout.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <div class="bg-muted mt-6 rounded-2xl p-4">
          <p class="text-muted-foreground text-xs tracking-[0.16em] uppercase">
            Built for merchants
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm">
            Product-linked try-on history, cache-aware generations, and
            provider-agnostic architecture so your app can evolve without vendor
            lock-in.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-20 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="bg-card rounded-2xl border p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold">Conversion confidence</h3>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Shoppers can visualize fit intent and style alignment directly on
          their own image before adding to cart.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="bg-card rounded-2xl border p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold">Lower operating waste</h3>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Cache re-use and one-credit-per-generation policies are designed to
          keep provider spend predictable.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="bg-card rounded-2xl border p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold">Future-proof stack</h3>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Provider gateways let you swap AI engines (Fashn, Vertex, Gemini, and
          others) without rewriting storefront integration.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section
      class="bg-card orb-shadow mt-20 rounded-3xl border p-8"
      id="pricing"
    >
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold">Commercial Model</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-3 max-w-3xl">
        Start with credit packs for immediate activation. Grow into
        subscriptions or enterprise terms as usage scales.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border p-4">
          <p class="text-muted-foreground text-xs tracking-[0.16em] uppercase">
            Starter
          </p>
          <p class="font-display mt-2 text-2xl font-bold">On-demand credits</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2 text-sm">
            Fast testing and pilot stores.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border p-4">
          <p class="text-muted-foreground text-xs tracking-[0.16em] uppercase">
            Growth
          </p>
          <p class="font-display mt-2 text-2xl font-bold">
            Monthly subscription
          </p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2 text-sm">
            Predictable budget with usage bands.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border p-4">
          <p class="text-muted-foreground text-xs tracking-[0.16em] uppercase">
            Enterprise
          </p>
          <p class="font-display mt-2 text-2xl font-bold">Custom terms</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2 text-sm">
            Dedicated support and tailored flows.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
